WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:05.797
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:06.881
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Pig!</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.176 --> 00:10.552
<i>Goat!</i>

00:10.635 --> 00:13.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:14.806
<i>Banana!</i>

00:14.889 --> 00:19.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:19.561 --> 00:20.770
<i>Cricket!</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:28.153
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
- A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
<i>all:</i>
<i>Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!</i>

00:41.624 --> 00:44.586
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:44.669 --> 00:50.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.800 --> 00:52.552
[crow cawing]

00:52.635 --> 00:54.971
<i>- Look, you can see</i>
<i>our house from here.</i>

00:55.054 --> 00:56.556
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:56.639 --> 01:01.311
<i>[lively music]</i>

01:01.394 --> 01:03.521
- What are these for, anyway?

01:03.605 --> 01:06.816
- I'm going to be discovered
by a famous movie director.

01:06.900 --> 01:10.653
{\an1}So why not sprinkle
a few of my headshots around

01:10.737 --> 01:11.654
while we're here?

01:11.738 --> 01:13.198
That's what I always say!

01:13.281 --> 01:15.408
[radio static]
- Uhh.

01:15.492 --> 01:18.495
Hello, and welcome to
Broseph Brothers' movie studio.

01:18.578 --> 01:21.331
Can everyone give me ten bucks?
I lost my wallet.

01:21.414 --> 01:22.874
Uhh.

01:22.957 --> 01:24.334
[tires squealing]

01:24.417 --> 01:28.129
- So this is where all
the show biz magic happens.

01:32.717 --> 01:36.638
Banana, what are you watching?
You're missing the tour!

01:36.721 --> 01:39.098
{\an3}- Only the greatest
TV show ever made, ever:

01:39.182 --> 01:41.017
"Cow Duck Avocado Mantis"!

01:41.100 --> 01:43.812
<i>[rock music]</i>

01:43.895 --> 01:47.690
- I wish there was some dingus
to throw this birthday cake at!

01:47.774 --> 01:49.275
{\an1}- Hello.

01:49.359 --> 01:50.527
<i>[studio audience cheers]</i>

01:50.610 --> 01:51.903
- Ooh!

01:51.986 --> 01:55.865
Sweet poppa's porkchops!

01:55.949 --> 01:56.825
[doorbell rings]

01:56.908 --> 01:57.867
<i>[studio audience laughs]</i>

01:57.951 --> 01:59.410
- [laughs]

01:59.494 --> 02:00.787
[coughs]

02:00.870 --> 02:02.997
Ah--he's got the
best catchphrase, ever!

02:03.081 --> 02:04.541
- Look, Banana!

02:04.624 --> 02:07.460
{\an1}They're filming "Cow Duck
Avocado Mantis" right there!

02:07.544 --> 02:09.711
- Movies make me constipated.

02:09.795 --> 02:14.968
- You mean my TV hero Avocado is
inside that building right now?

02:15.051 --> 02:16.678
It's autograph time!

02:16.761 --> 02:18.721
[tires screech]

02:18.805 --> 02:19.722
<i>- Banana!</i>

02:19.806 --> 02:20.598
{\an1}- Oh! Ah!

02:20.682 --> 02:21.599
{\an3}Oh!

02:21.683 --> 02:24.060
{\an3}[groans]

02:24.143 --> 02:25.186
{\an3}[moans]

02:27.105 --> 02:28.314
Mm, Duck's dressing room--
don't care.

02:28.398 --> 02:31.150
Cow's dressing room--
he's a hack.

02:31.234 --> 02:32.694
Here it is:

02:32.777 --> 02:36.489
the coolest, most awesome TV
character of all time!

02:36.573 --> 02:38.575
Avocado!

02:43.162 --> 02:45.290
- [coughs]

02:47.959 --> 02:50.962
[yawning]

02:58.553 --> 02:59.762
- You're not Avocado!

02:59.846 --> 03:01.014
What are you doing here?

03:01.097 --> 03:03.808
This is Avocado's dressing room,
you ugly pit!

03:03.892 --> 03:06.978
- Excuse me, but I am
the great Avocado,

03:07.061 --> 03:08.938
actor extraordinaire,
and I--

03:09.022 --> 03:09.939
- You filthy liar!

03:10.023 --> 03:11.190
- Oh!

03:11.274 --> 03:13.026
Sweet poppa's porkchops.

03:13.109 --> 03:14.861
[moans]

03:14.944 --> 03:15.820
{\an3}Oh!

03:15.904 --> 03:16.946
{\an3}[moans]

03:20.033 --> 03:22.619
Sweet poppa's porkchops.

03:22.702 --> 03:23.620
- Huh?

03:23.703 --> 03:25.330
Uh-oh.

03:25.413 --> 03:27.123
He really is Avocado.

03:27.206 --> 03:28.291
Why didn't you say something?

03:28.374 --> 03:30.919
{\an1}Hey, hey, hey, Avocado!
Wakey-wakey!

03:31.836 --> 03:34.130
- [grunting]

03:34.213 --> 03:37.133
- Desperate times call
for desperate mouth-to-mouth.

03:37.216 --> 03:38.426
[exhaling rapidly]

03:40.553 --> 03:41.971
- [muttering]
Hey.

03:42.055 --> 03:43.681
Those are my teeth.

03:45.683 --> 03:47.477
- Whoops.
Oh, sorry!

03:47.560 --> 03:48.227
Mr. Avocado, sir,

03:48.311 --> 03:50.063
I'm your biggest fan.

03:50.146 --> 03:51.230
Can I have your autograph?

03:51.314 --> 03:52.649
[knock at door]

03:52.732 --> 03:54.233
<i>- Avocado!</i>
<i>You're on in 30 seconds!</i>

03:54.317 --> 03:56.152
- [as Avocado]
Be right there,

03:56.235 --> 03:57.570
mister director, sir!

03:57.654 --> 03:58.655
[normal voice]
Hey, wake up, wake up!

03:58.738 --> 04:01.115
- And don't be late,
you old slob,

04:01.199 --> 04:02.867
or you're fired!

04:02.951 --> 04:05.411
- Avocado fired?

04:07.747 --> 04:10.291
Not on my watch!

04:10.375 --> 04:12.669
You're lucky I'm here to pick up
the pieces of this mess

04:12.752 --> 04:14.337
I'm completely responsible for!

04:14.420 --> 04:17.130
{\an3}- Uh, oh.
Wait, I think I'm okay.

04:17.214 --> 04:19.007
[grunts]
Oh!

04:19.091 --> 04:20.760
[trophies crashing]

04:20.843 --> 04:24.639
{\an3}[yelping]

04:29.852 --> 04:33.481
<i>[rock music]</i>

04:33.564 --> 04:34.816
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Cow!</i>

04:34.899 --> 04:37.819
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:37.902 --> 04:39.028
<i>Duck!</i>

04:39.112 --> 04:42.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:42.699 --> 04:43.866
<i>Avocado!</i>

04:43.950 --> 04:45.535
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:45.618 --> 04:47.036
<i>Mantis!</i>

04:47.120 --> 04:50.039
all: Cow Duck Avocado Mantis!

04:50.123 --> 04:52.500
[studio audience cheering]

04:57.547 --> 04:58.798
- Let's play "Twenty Questions"!

04:58.881 --> 05:04.095
I'm thinking of the biggest jerk
in the entire universe!

05:04.178 --> 05:05.888
[cheers and applause]

05:05.972 --> 05:07.932
- Whoo!
Whoo!

05:08.016 --> 05:09.684
- Sweet pa...

05:09.767 --> 05:13.396
[gasps]

05:13.479 --> 05:16.524
[whimpering]

05:17.775 --> 05:19.068
- Hey, Avocado!

05:19.152 --> 05:22.739
You're late for game night!
Kuhh...

05:22.822 --> 05:24.907
[laughter]

05:24.991 --> 05:27.535
- I, uh--

05:27.618 --> 05:30.913
- [whispering]
Say your line!

05:30.997 --> 05:33.833
{\an8}- My line?
Uh.

05:33.916 --> 05:36.753
{\an8}- "Sweet poppa's porkchops,"
<i>mon!</i>

05:36.836 --> 05:41.257
{\an3}- I said, "Why are you
late for game night, Avocado?"

05:41.340 --> 05:42.550
{\an1}- [gulps]

05:42.633 --> 05:45.678
[audience jeering]

05:46.846 --> 05:49.057
{\an3}- Hey, Avocado!
How about a pretzel?

05:49.140 --> 05:50.808
{\an1}- [as Avocado]
Um, sure!

05:50.892 --> 05:54.687
[laughter]

05:55.354 --> 05:58.858
- I mean, a leg pretzel!

05:58.941 --> 05:59.942
<i>[ragtime music]</i>

06:00.026 --> 06:01.110
- [yelps]

06:01.194 --> 06:02.278
[audience laughter]

06:02.361 --> 06:03.946
[screams]

06:04.030 --> 06:05.948
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:06.032 --> 06:07.366
- [laughs]

06:07.450 --> 06:08.493
Oh!

06:10.828 --> 06:13.790
[audience laughter continues]

06:13.873 --> 06:19.462
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:19.545 --> 06:22.632
- [as Avocado]
Sweet poppa's porkchops!

06:22.715 --> 06:24.842
[laughter and cheering]

06:24.926 --> 06:27.762
{\an3}- Avocado, ready to go
for a spin?

06:27.845 --> 06:29.806
- No!

06:29.889 --> 06:30.973
But you are!

06:31.057 --> 06:33.851
- My glasses!
My glasses!

06:35.103 --> 06:35.812
[laughter]

06:35.895 --> 06:38.481
{\an3}[yelps]

06:38.564 --> 06:41.317
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:41.400 --> 06:42.318
Oh!

06:42.401 --> 06:43.736
{\an3}- [yelping]

06:43.820 --> 06:46.280
{\an3}Ahh!

06:46.364 --> 06:48.116
- That's not in the script!

06:48.199 --> 06:50.326
{\an1}- [laughs]
It is now!

06:50.409 --> 06:52.328
- Whoa!

06:52.411 --> 06:53.329
[screams]

06:53.412 --> 06:55.665
[grunts]

06:55.748 --> 06:56.165
- Oh!

06:56.249 --> 06:59.168
- [laughs]

06:59.252 --> 07:02.213
<i>[theme music playing]</i>

07:02.296 --> 07:03.965
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:04.048 --> 07:07.009
I'm Avocado, baby!

07:07.093 --> 07:08.344
- You!

07:08.427 --> 07:09.679
[audience gasps]

07:09.762 --> 07:12.473
Give me back my costume!

07:12.557 --> 07:14.142
<i>[theme music plays]</i>

07:14.225 --> 07:15.810
- Avocado, you lazy pit!

07:15.893 --> 07:19.063
Getting someone to fill in
for you while you take a nap!

07:19.147 --> 07:21.691
[unintelligible yelling]

07:21.774 --> 07:23.568
You're fired!

07:23.651 --> 07:25.111
- But--no--don't blame him!

07:25.194 --> 07:26.737
I was just trying to help!

07:26.821 --> 07:28.573
I'm the one you should fire.

07:28.656 --> 07:31.033
- Oh, that's really nice.

07:31.117 --> 07:31.742
- Thanks.

07:31.826 --> 07:33.369
- You're fired too!

07:33.452 --> 07:35.580
[laughter]

07:35.663 --> 07:38.249
- This may not be the best time.

07:38.332 --> 07:39.876
Can I have an autograph?

07:39.959 --> 07:41.878
- Sure.

07:41.961 --> 07:45.047
[audience laughter fades]

07:48.092 --> 07:49.302
{\an3}- Ah!

07:49.385 --> 07:50.511
- I'll get you!

07:50.595 --> 07:52.388
You ruined my life!
- [screaming]

07:52.471 --> 07:53.806
<i>[lively music]</i>

07:53.890 --> 07:55.057
- Huh, and up ahead on the right
is our world-famous

07:55.141 --> 07:57.393
Belt Hall of Fame.

07:57.476 --> 08:00.313
My mother-in-law wears
a world record-size belt.

08:00.396 --> 08:02.398
Uhh, personal life.

08:02.481 --> 08:04.317
- The Belt Hall of Fame?

08:04.400 --> 08:06.819
That's my favorite!

08:06.903 --> 08:07.820
Whee!

08:07.904 --> 08:08.988
<i>- Pig!</i>

08:11.449 --> 08:12.992
- Wow!

08:13.075 --> 08:16.913
All my favorite movie belts
right here under one roof!

08:16.996 --> 08:18.289
Ooh!

08:18.372 --> 08:20.625
The belt from
"Revenge of the Pantsuit."

08:20.708 --> 08:22.251
[gasps]
And here's the belt from

08:22.335 --> 08:26.088
"Revenge of the Pantsuit 2:
Electric Suit-A-Loo!"

08:26.172 --> 08:28.925
And an empty spot.

08:30.760 --> 08:33.596
Some day I'll be in here too.

08:33.679 --> 08:37.642
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

08:37.725 --> 08:41.062
♪ One day I'll find my place ♪

08:41.145 --> 08:44.774
♪ Racing in this crazy race ♪

08:44.857 --> 08:46.776
- Hey, pal, no singing!

08:46.859 --> 08:47.610
- Hey.

08:47.693 --> 08:49.403
- This is the Belt Hall of Fame,

08:49.487 --> 08:51.822
{\an1}not the Rock and Roll
Hall of Fame!

08:51.906 --> 08:53.741
Just sit here like a belt!

08:53.824 --> 08:55.993
{\an1}Come on!
I like belts!

08:58.579 --> 09:00.831
<i>[triumphant fanfare]</i>

09:00.915 --> 09:04.502
- Whoa.

09:04.585 --> 09:08.631
Hello, I'm looking to be a belt
in the movie industry.

09:08.714 --> 09:10.091
{\an1}- What are you,
out of your mind?

09:10.174 --> 09:11.801
{\an1}You're a pig!
That's the opposite of a belt.

09:11.884 --> 09:13.344
{\an1}Come back when
you're not insane,

09:13.427 --> 09:14.679
and then still don't come back!

09:14.762 --> 09:18.307
- [stuttering] B-b-b-b-but...
my dreams.

09:18.391 --> 09:21.310
- Okay, and action!

09:21.394 --> 09:24.814
- I'm Stink Naugahyde, and
I'm here to save the universe...

09:24.897 --> 09:26.649
right after this hot dog...

09:26.732 --> 09:27.567
[chomping]

09:27.650 --> 09:29.652
And this hot dog...

09:29.735 --> 09:31.153
and this hot dog...

09:31.237 --> 09:33.239
and this hot dog.

09:33.322 --> 09:35.032
Ohh.

09:35.116 --> 09:36.742
Ugh.

09:36.826 --> 09:37.326
[seams tearing]

09:37.410 --> 09:39.412
[all gasping]

09:39.495 --> 09:40.538
- Don't look at me.
Don't look at me!

09:40.621 --> 09:43.082
Ah, I need a new belt,
and fast!

09:43.165 --> 09:44.500
- Oh, boy!

09:44.583 --> 09:47.378
His big belt bust
is my big belt break!

09:50.339 --> 09:51.465
- Hey, I thought I told you to--

09:51.549 --> 09:52.550
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

09:52.633 --> 09:54.051
Let's give the kid a chance.

09:54.135 --> 09:55.594
- Thanks, Stink!

09:55.678 --> 09:56.971
- Okay, all right,
whatever you say, Mr. Naugahyde.

09:57.054 --> 09:59.181
Action!

09:59.265 --> 10:02.518
- Professor Blubber Brain,
you asked for it!

10:02.601 --> 10:06.063
Get ready to be flab-slapped!

10:06.147 --> 10:07.982
{\an3}[yelping]

10:08.065 --> 10:10.067
- [grunts]
I can do this!

10:10.151 --> 10:11.902
[grunts]

10:11.986 --> 10:14.196
Must hold up pants.

10:14.280 --> 10:16.407
{\an3}[screams]

10:16.490 --> 10:17.533
[screaming]
Oh!

10:17.616 --> 10:18.868
{\an3}- Oh, no!

10:18.951 --> 10:20.077
- Don't look at me.
Don't look at me!

10:20.161 --> 10:21.537
[all gasping]

10:21.620 --> 10:24.290
{\an3}- I'm sorry, Stink.
I let you down.

10:24.373 --> 10:26.876
- You didn't just let me down;
you let my pants down!

10:26.959 --> 10:28.294
You let the crew down!

10:28.377 --> 10:30.338
But most importantly,
you let my pants down!

10:30.421 --> 10:32.673
- You're washed up, Pig!

10:32.757 --> 10:35.843
You'll never be a belt
in this town again!

10:35.926 --> 10:38.846
- [cries]

10:38.929 --> 10:40.848
{\an3}[sobbing]

10:40.931 --> 10:42.808
[water pattering]

10:42.892 --> 10:44.477
I'm a failure,

10:44.560 --> 10:46.771
{\an3}just another mixed-up pig
who tried to be

10:46.854 --> 10:50.066
a famous movie belt,
but couldn't hack it!

10:50.149 --> 10:52.860
{\an3}[crying]

10:52.943 --> 10:55.154
[mice squeaking]

10:55.237 --> 10:57.907
Hey, buddy.
Here you go.

10:57.990 --> 11:01.452
Come on, guys, reach for it.

11:01.535 --> 11:03.537
You guys are good stretchers!

11:03.621 --> 11:06.499
I wish I was more like you.

11:06.582 --> 11:07.500
Heh!

11:07.583 --> 11:10.211
[groans]
Ideas hurt my head!

11:12.505 --> 11:14.757
- Sorry, everyone.
The movie's canceled.

11:14.840 --> 11:15.966
<i>all: Aww.</i>

11:16.050 --> 11:17.676
- I busted every belt in town.

11:17.760 --> 11:18.594
[cries]

11:18.677 --> 11:20.429
- Not every belt!

11:20.513 --> 11:22.473
[screams]

11:22.556 --> 11:23.724
- You again?

11:23.808 --> 11:25.976
- Haven't had enough
failure for one day?

11:26.060 --> 11:27.186
- Don't worry, guys!

11:27.269 --> 11:30.022
I have a little
sleeve up my surprise!

11:30.106 --> 11:31.440
Lights!

11:31.524 --> 11:32.775
Camera!

11:32.858 --> 11:34.151
Belt!

11:34.235 --> 11:36.904
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

11:36.987 --> 11:39.782
- Professor Blubber Brain,
eat my flab!

11:39.865 --> 11:41.158
[flab wobbling]

11:41.242 --> 11:44.078
- You can count on me, Stink!

11:44.161 --> 11:46.372
- [grunting]

11:46.455 --> 11:48.707
- [groaning]

11:48.791 --> 11:50.793
- Oh!
I can't look!

11:50.876 --> 11:51.961
Rolling.

11:52.044 --> 11:53.796
- Oh!
Ready, rats?

11:53.879 --> 11:56.298
It's stretchy time!

11:56.382 --> 11:58.175
<i>[heroic music]</i>

11:58.259 --> 12:00.928
[grunting]

12:02.972 --> 12:05.182
- Now prepare yourself,
Blubber Brain!

12:05.266 --> 12:10.062
Get ready to be
Fla-a-a-ab-slapped!

12:10.146 --> 12:11.689
{\an1}- [yelps]

12:11.772 --> 12:14.733
- Wow!
Cut and print!

12:14.817 --> 12:16.610
- You did it.
Pig, you did the impossible!

12:16.694 --> 12:18.487
Oh,
you kept my pants up!

12:18.571 --> 12:20.906
- Give me five, Stink!

12:20.990 --> 12:23.409
- Let's make that ten!

12:23.492 --> 12:24.243
- [yelps]

12:24.326 --> 12:26.287
[screaming]

12:26.370 --> 12:27.913
[glass shatters]

12:27.997 --> 12:30.166
The Belt Hall of Fame!

12:34.295 --> 12:37.465
Wait, you mean
I've got to stay in here?

12:37.548 --> 12:38.799
Hello?

12:38.883 --> 12:41.469
Anybody?
Belt Hall of Fame curator?

12:41.552 --> 12:43.971
I'm all alone!

12:46.849 --> 12:48.517
♪ I'm all alone ♪

12:48.601 --> 12:51.270
♪ Away from my home ♪

12:51.353 --> 12:52.480
♪ And no ♪

12:52.563 --> 12:54.398
- What'd I tell you?

12:54.482 --> 12:56.525
No singing in here!

12:56.609 --> 12:57.485
- Sorry.

12:57.568 --> 12:59.111
I'm a musical pig.

12:59.195 --> 13:01.530
{\an3}- Uh, who made these chairs,
Dracula?

13:01.614 --> 13:04.283
{\an3}Oh, hey Dracula.
Uhh.

13:04.366 --> 13:06.660
{\an1}- I have been
on this movie lot all day,

13:06.744 --> 13:07.995
and I haven't been

13:08.078 --> 13:10.706
{\an1}discovered by a single
famous movie director yet.

13:10.789 --> 13:12.875
{\an3}- Oh, Goat.
[chuckles]

13:12.958 --> 13:15.211
{\an3}You know that never
happens in real life.

13:15.294 --> 13:16.378
- [sniffles]

13:16.462 --> 13:17.713
- I'm a famous movie director,

13:17.796 --> 13:20.508
and I'm discovering you now!

13:20.591 --> 13:21.675
- Stop the tram!

13:21.759 --> 13:22.843
[brakes squeal]
- Ah!

13:24.178 --> 13:25.137
<i>- Goat!</i>
- Ah!

13:25.221 --> 13:26.805
- Right in the head!

13:26.889 --> 13:28.974
[light shatters]

13:29.058 --> 13:30.809
- You've got the look!

13:30.893 --> 13:31.977
- I do?

13:32.061 --> 13:33.562
I do!

13:33.646 --> 13:34.813
- Are you a good screamer?

13:34.897 --> 13:36.899
- Do you consider this good?

13:36.982 --> 13:39.902
[high-pitched scream]

13:39.985 --> 13:42.238
Whoopsie dingles.

13:42.321 --> 13:43.781
- You're hired!

13:43.864 --> 13:47.243
You're gonna be in my new
horror flick, "Jack Face!"

13:47.326 --> 13:48.285
- Yes!

13:48.369 --> 13:49.828
Am I Jack?
- No.

13:49.912 --> 13:51.247
- Am I Face?
- No.

13:51.330 --> 13:53.082
{\an3}- You're Scared Sorority Girl
Number Two.

13:53.165 --> 13:54.375
{\an1}- Yes!
Oh.

13:54.458 --> 13:56.335
{\an3}- But that's supposed
to be my part!

13:56.418 --> 13:58.420
{\an3}I'm Scared Sorority
Girl Number Two!

13:58.504 --> 14:00.172
- Not anymore, Twinklepipes!

14:00.256 --> 14:01.840
Now it's Goat.

14:01.924 --> 14:04.635
{\an1}- Sorry, Lila.
You know I'm your biggest fan.

14:04.718 --> 14:07.930
{\an3}- Well, I'm not yours.
You're hideous and horrible.

14:08.013 --> 14:09.306
- Wait, what?

14:09.390 --> 14:12.351
{\an3}- I'm gonna...
[grumbling]

14:12.434 --> 14:13.561
{\an1}- Text me!

14:13.644 --> 14:16.480
<i>[sinister music]</i>

14:16.564 --> 14:17.773
- Ah.

14:19.567 --> 14:20.859
Ah!

14:20.943 --> 14:22.444
- [laughs]

14:22.528 --> 14:24.572
Nobody takes my part, Goat--

14:24.655 --> 14:25.698
<i>nobody.</i>

14:25.781 --> 14:27.533
[lightning strikes,
cackling]

14:27.616 --> 14:29.868
<i>[scary music]</i>

14:29.952 --> 14:32.705
<i>[screeching violins]</i>

14:33.831 --> 14:36.250
- OMG.
It sure is dark outside.

14:36.333 --> 14:37.835
And I'm adorable.

14:37.918 --> 14:41.880
I sure would hate it if someone
stuck a meat cleaver in my head.

14:41.964 --> 14:42.881
{\an3}- Ah!

14:42.965 --> 14:44.383
- Excuse me.

14:44.466 --> 14:46.635
I know the script says
that I should run and scream,

14:46.719 --> 14:49.096
but I don't really feel
Sorority Girl Number Two

14:49.179 --> 14:50.598
would be so wimpy.

14:50.681 --> 14:52.891
I mean--can you keep it down?
I'm giving notes.

14:52.975 --> 14:55.477
- Hmm, so what do you think
Scared Sorority Girl Number Two

14:55.561 --> 14:56.562
would do?

14:56.645 --> 14:57.813
- Something like this.

14:57.896 --> 15:00.899
[grunts, glass shatters]

15:00.983 --> 15:02.526
- Ow!

15:02.610 --> 15:04.320
Ah!

15:04.403 --> 15:05.654
- Uh, no.

15:05.738 --> 15:07.531
Just stick to the script,
sweetheart.

15:07.615 --> 15:08.824
- Will do, honey cakes.

15:08.907 --> 15:10.075
- Still rolling!

15:10.159 --> 15:12.953
- Goat's head
is gonna be rolling.

15:13.037 --> 15:13.954
- And action!

15:14.038 --> 15:15.164
- [screaming]

15:15.247 --> 15:16.165
{\an3}- [screams]

15:16.248 --> 15:17.166
- [screaming]

15:17.249 --> 15:18.417
- [screaming]

15:18.500 --> 15:19.418
- [screaming]

15:19.501 --> 15:20.919
- [screaming]

15:21.003 --> 15:22.171
- Shark attack!

15:22.254 --> 15:23.756
{\an1}- [yelps]

15:23.839 --> 15:25.924
- I think that works much
better, don't you?

15:26.008 --> 15:27.259
- Oh, for the love of--

15:27.343 --> 15:28.886
Goat, what do you think
you're doing?

15:28.969 --> 15:30.512
- Improving your movie.

15:30.596 --> 15:33.432
{\an3}Okay, I was thinking, what if
Jack Face snuck up on me,

15:33.515 --> 15:36.769
kind of like this--wah!

15:36.852 --> 15:39.021
- Jack Face, keep doing
what you're doing!

15:39.104 --> 15:41.357
This is fantastic!

15:41.440 --> 15:42.775
- [groaning]

15:42.858 --> 15:44.026
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold up, hold up.

15:44.109 --> 15:45.653
You are doing it great.
Oh, yes, you are.

15:45.736 --> 15:48.197
But how about like this?
- Oh!

15:48.280 --> 15:49.823
Ah!

15:49.907 --> 15:51.950
{\an3}- Now you try!
Go ahead!

15:53.619 --> 15:55.496
{\an3}Great!

15:55.579 --> 15:56.872
{\an1}Awesome!

15:56.955 --> 15:58.040
[groans]
Fantastic!

15:58.123 --> 16:01.877
Oh, you are so good at this.

16:03.253 --> 16:06.465
- Really?
- Lila Twinklepipes?

16:06.548 --> 16:08.634
- That was the greatest acting
I've ever seen!

16:08.717 --> 16:10.928
Goat, you're out,
and Lila's in!

16:11.011 --> 16:13.889
She's going to play Jack Face
and Sorority Girl Number Two,

16:13.972 --> 16:15.015
so, uh!

16:15.099 --> 16:16.058
{\an3}- What?

16:16.141 --> 16:17.476
{\an1}- Great, but I have
one condition.

16:17.559 --> 16:18.977
{\an3}- Name it!

16:19.061 --> 16:20.396
- You're out, and Goat's in!
- Huh?

16:20.479 --> 16:21.814
- Girlfriend, I am so impressed!

16:21.897 --> 16:24.233
You've got great
directorial instincts.

16:24.316 --> 16:28.195
- Oh, I got directorial
instincts up the wazoo!

16:28.278 --> 16:30.364
- Hey!
- And five, people!

16:30.447 --> 16:32.866
Go get me a Grand-ey
Quinoa Frappè-gavè.

16:32.950 --> 16:34.284
- Milk and sugar?

16:34.368 --> 16:36.912
- And take my dog for a walk,
and buy me a dog.

16:36.995 --> 16:39.581
And then sell it.
I'm tired of the dog.

16:39.665 --> 16:41.583
- Uhh, do you like
special effects?

16:41.667 --> 16:43.210
{\an3}I don't.

16:43.293 --> 16:46.505
- These movies are all terrible.
I could do way better!

16:46.588 --> 16:48.465
[grunts]
Huh?

16:49.800 --> 16:50.676
Cliff?

16:50.759 --> 16:53.846
[screaming]
Cliff!

16:55.514 --> 16:57.266
[explosion]

16:57.349 --> 17:00.269
- If anyone needs a wart
removed, I know a guy.

17:00.352 --> 17:02.604
Anybody?
Don't be shy.

17:02.688 --> 17:04.732
Uhh.

17:04.815 --> 17:06.567
<i>- Cricket!</i>

17:06.650 --> 17:07.901
- It's been my lifelong dream

17:07.984 --> 17:10.194
to create the world's
greatest movie!

17:10.279 --> 17:12.573
But where am I gonna find
the world's greatest director,

17:12.656 --> 17:14.950
actors,
sound guy, stunt guy?

17:15.032 --> 17:16.242
Oh, yeah!
Right here!

17:16.326 --> 17:17.994
Me!
Me, me, me, me, me!

17:18.078 --> 17:19.872
And me!
[laughs]

17:19.954 --> 17:21.373
But I'm just one lone cricket.

17:21.457 --> 17:23.291
I can't do all
of those things at once!

17:23.375 --> 17:25.335
[gasps]
Or can I?

17:25.419 --> 17:28.630
I'll just put my
Thorapic Ongometer Clone setting

17:28.714 --> 17:31.341
on high and...

17:31.425 --> 17:33.010
Holy clone-y!

17:33.093 --> 17:34.511
{\an1}[laughs]

17:34.595 --> 17:36.096
{\an3}- [laughs]

17:37.931 --> 17:39.641
[all laughing]

17:39.725 --> 17:42.186
[Thorapic Ongometer booming]

17:42.269 --> 17:45.063
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

17:45.147 --> 17:46.774
- You two look great!

17:46.857 --> 17:48.776
Just a couple of final touches.

17:48.859 --> 17:50.319
- Why do I have to wear the wig?

17:50.402 --> 17:52.571
- Because I'm the director,
and what I say goes.

17:52.654 --> 17:55.324
- And who made you the director?
- I did.

17:55.407 --> 17:58.243
{\an3}Okay, so you two are saying
good-bye to each other

17:58.327 --> 18:00.204
and kissing for the last time.

18:00.287 --> 18:01.830
{\an3}And action!

18:03.499 --> 18:04.917
{\an3}And cut!
What's the problem?

18:05.000 --> 18:07.211
{\an1}- I don't want to kiss myself.
It's weird.

18:07.294 --> 18:09.963
{\an3}- Come on, guys!
You're supposed to be in love.

18:10.047 --> 18:12.591
{\an3}You need to show that love
with a kiss!

18:12.674 --> 18:14.510
{\an1}- Yeah, uh, no,
not gonna happen.

18:14.593 --> 18:16.303
{\an3}- Please, Cricket.
You're being difficult.

18:16.386 --> 18:18.305
{\an3}Why can't you be
more like this Cricket?

18:18.388 --> 18:20.265
{\an3}He doesn't have
a problem with this.

18:20.349 --> 18:22.559
- Of course I do!
Think I want to kiss that?

18:22.643 --> 18:24.853
He's weird-looking!
- And you ain't?

18:24.937 --> 18:26.188
{\an3}- Now, now,
you're both

18:26.271 --> 18:28.106
{\an3}the most handsome
actors in the world!

18:28.190 --> 18:29.274
I made sure of that!

18:29.358 --> 18:30.776
- Then why don't you kiss him?

18:30.859 --> 18:33.570
{\an3}- Because that's not my job.
It's yours.

18:33.654 --> 18:35.697
- Then I want your job.

18:35.781 --> 18:37.950
{\an3}- Kiss, you Crickets!
Kiss!

18:38.033 --> 18:39.451
- Why should we listen to you?

18:39.535 --> 18:41.662
{\an3}- Because I made you!
I'm Cricket!

18:41.745 --> 18:42.746
{\an1}both:
So are we!

18:42.830 --> 18:44.289
{\an3}- Yeah, but I'm
the real Cricket!

18:44.373 --> 18:45.874
{\an1}- And cut.
Perfect, guys!

18:45.958 --> 18:47.209
Just what I wanted:

18:47.292 --> 18:49.545
{\an1}a bunch of Crickets arguing
about not kissing.

18:49.628 --> 18:51.255
All of you clones were great!

18:51.338 --> 18:52.631
{\an3}- What?
I--I'm not a clone!

18:52.714 --> 18:54.091
I'm the real Cricket!

18:54.174 --> 18:56.510
{\an1}- Let's try that one more time,
and you keep thinking

18:56.593 --> 18:57.553
you're the real Cricket.

18:57.636 --> 18:58.512
It's precious!

18:58.595 --> 19:00.013
- But I am the real Cricket!

19:00.097 --> 19:01.098
{\an1}- Love it!

19:01.181 --> 19:02.891
{\an1}But save it for the camera.
And action!

19:02.975 --> 19:05.602
{\an3}- Excuse me, but I've been
sitting here, listening to your

19:05.686 --> 19:07.896
{\an3}clone-y baloney lies
long enough!

19:07.980 --> 19:09.231
I'm the real Cricket!

19:09.314 --> 19:10.858
- You?
Oh, please!

19:10.941 --> 19:12.276
{\an3}- Yeah, me!

19:12.359 --> 19:13.360
{\an3}both: Ow!

19:13.443 --> 19:14.736
{\an1}- And cut!

19:14.820 --> 19:16.864
Just what I wanted: a movie
about Cricket clones arguing

19:16.947 --> 19:18.198
about who the real Cricket is,

19:18.282 --> 19:20.409
{\an1}while making a movie about
Crickets not kissing!

19:20.492 --> 19:24.121
- Maybe your movie, but in my
movie, they're supposed to kiss!

19:24.204 --> 19:25.163
- Your movie?

19:25.247 --> 19:26.331
- [smooching]

19:26.415 --> 19:28.208
- Now--wait--now you're kissing?

19:28.292 --> 19:29.418
All right, roll film!

19:29.501 --> 19:31.086
- No, cut, cut, cut, cut!

19:31.169 --> 19:32.754
Who let this Cricket in here?

19:32.838 --> 19:34.089
{\an3}- And cut!
Perfect!

19:34.173 --> 19:36.675
{\an3}Just what I wanted!
Complete Cricket clone chaos!

19:36.758 --> 19:40.429
all: No!
Me, I'm the real Cricket!

19:41.597 --> 19:42.514
- I'll get you!

19:42.598 --> 19:43.473
- [panting]

19:43.557 --> 19:45.809
- You ruined my life!

19:45.893 --> 19:47.936
{\an3}- [screams]

19:48.020 --> 19:49.229
- Come back here!
[grunts]

19:50.856 --> 19:52.566
- [heavy breathing]

19:54.192 --> 19:55.944
[screams]

19:56.028 --> 19:58.322
{\an1}Goat!
What are you doing here?

19:58.405 --> 20:00.991
{\an3}- I'm here to find the perfect
belt for my next picture.

20:01.074 --> 20:02.034
{\an3}- Hello?

20:02.117 --> 20:03.243
- Pig!

20:05.704 --> 20:07.414
- [gasps]

20:07.497 --> 20:09.041
Thanks for letting me out!

20:09.124 --> 20:10.792
Breathing's my favorite!

20:10.876 --> 20:12.586
- Let's get out of here!

20:15.213 --> 20:18.133
{\an3}Ah--actually,
through the other door.

20:18.216 --> 20:20.469
- I wonder where Cricket is.

20:21.386 --> 20:23.138
- I resent that remark!

20:23.221 --> 20:25.432
- No, I'm the real Cricket!
The real Cricket doesn't have...

20:25.515 --> 20:28.644
[all speaking at once]

20:28.727 --> 20:30.312
- You got to help me!

20:30.395 --> 20:32.981
{\an3}I made all these clones, and now
they're trying to replace me!

20:33.065 --> 20:35.275
- Don't listen to him!
I'm the real Cricket!

20:35.359 --> 20:37.486
- No, I'm the real Cricket!

20:37.569 --> 20:39.905
- Which one is the real Cricket?

20:39.988 --> 20:41.156
- We need our friend back!

20:41.240 --> 20:43.659
{\an3}- Who cares?
Just grab one; let's go!

20:43.742 --> 20:45.869
- We can't just grab any!

20:45.953 --> 20:47.496
{\an1}[gasps]
I got it!

20:47.579 --> 20:49.039
Good thing I brought my guitar.

20:49.122 --> 20:51.625
- Good thing I brought
my earplugs!

20:53.168 --> 20:54.836
[Crickets chattering
indistinctly]

20:54.920 --> 20:58.840
- ♪ Unicorn whiskers,
gorilla tears ♪

20:58.924 --> 21:00.759
♪ Elf burps
and fairy slurps ♪

21:00.842 --> 21:02.177
- Huh?

21:02.260 --> 21:04.513
- ♪ Fiddle-de-dee,
dum, diddle-de-dum ♪

21:04.596 --> 21:05.681
- No!
Ah!

21:05.764 --> 21:08.850
- ♪ Chim-chiree,
diddily-dum ♪

21:08.934 --> 21:09.935
♪ Diddily-do ♪

21:10.018 --> 21:11.478
- Awful!

21:11.561 --> 21:14.523
- ♪ Chim-chim-chiree,
diddily-doo ♪

21:14.606 --> 21:15.857
- Make it stop!

21:15.941 --> 21:18.986
[Crickets exploding]

21:21.405 --> 21:22.614
- Yeah!

21:22.698 --> 21:25.617
- Goat, that's your
greatest song ever!

21:25.701 --> 21:29.204
- Oh, Cricket, I knew the real
you would appreciate my talent.

21:29.288 --> 21:30.497
- Hey, you!

21:30.580 --> 21:31.999
- [screams]

21:32.082 --> 21:33.125
[gulps]

21:33.208 --> 21:36.211
Please, sir!
All I wanted was your autograph!

21:36.294 --> 21:39.589
- You want an autograph?
Here's your autograph!

21:39.673 --> 21:41.216
- [groans]

21:43.677 --> 21:44.970
Look at this imprint!

21:45.053 --> 21:47.472
It's even better
than an autograph!

21:47.556 --> 21:50.517
Hey, guys, check it out!

21:50.600 --> 21:52.728
all: "Pig Goat Banana Cricket
punch in the face

21:52.811 --> 21:55.397
is better than an autograph"
high five!

21:55.480 --> 21:57.065
- And cut!

21:57.149 --> 21:59.693
{\an3}Just what I wanted!
That's a wrap!

22:01.945 --> 22:04.948
{\an8}<i>[gentle acoustic guitar music]</i>

22:05.032 --> 22:13.040
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:25.218 --> 22:27.971
{\an8}[whoopee cushion whistles]
